Yes, you  can describe arrays of complex types. Here's an example with a persons element containing n person elements:
<br />
<br />&lt;xs:element name="items"&gt;
<br />  &lt;xs:complexType&gt;
<br />    &lt;xs:sequence&gt;
<br />      &lt;xs:element name="item" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded"&gt;
<br />        &lt;xs:complexType&gt;
<br />          &lt;xs:sequence&gt;
<br />            ...
<br />          &lt;/xs:sequence&gt;
<br />        &lt;/xs:complexType&gt;
<br />      &lt;/xs:element&gt;
<br />    &lt;/xs:sequence&gt;
<br />  &lt;/xs:complexType&gt;
<br />&lt;/xs:element&gt;
<br />
<br />You could also make the item element a GED that's reused by reference.
