We also adopted most of the ideas presented here (I had forgotten to include the blockDefault="#all" bit).  
<br />
<br />One tools issue we ran into was that potential callers who want to create VS Web References weren't able to get .NET types created until we stuck a named complexType into the schema like this:
<br />
<br />&lt;xs:schema&gt;
<br />   &lt;!-- GED --&gt;
<br />   &lt;xs:element name="x"/&gt;
<br />
<br />   &lt;!-- Named type for VS XSD tool --&gt;
<br />   &lt;xs:complexType name="typeX"&gt;
<br />      &lt;xs:sequence&gt;
<br />         &lt;xs:element ref="tns:X"/&gt;
<br />      &lt;/xs:element&gt;
<br />   &lt;/xs:complexType&gt;
<br />
<br />&lt;/xs:schema&gt;
<br />
<br />I don't know if it's still an issue in Whidbey.
